        <p>As we continue our study of algebra, we'll encounter more and more expressions and equations with <term>exponents</term>, often containing unknown, variable values. The exponent rules are a quick list that remind us of how exponents work in a few specific situations. Let's work through <em>why</em> these rules work.</p>
    </subsection>

